  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>baby gammon joint</strong> to a pot of plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Continue to boil the <strong>baby gammon</strong>&nbsp;for 30 min or until it's cooked through</p>\r\n<p>Use the next 15 min to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>baby gammon</strong> has been cooking for 15 min, re-boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>conchiglie</strong> to a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the&nbsp;<strong>conchiglie</strong> for 6 min</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Roughly chop most of the<strong> pea shoots,&nbsp;</strong>saving the rest for garnish</p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> conchiglie</strong> has&nbsp;been cooking for&nbsp;6 min, add the <strong>garden peas</strong> and cook for a further 3 min&nbsp;or until they're cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>conchigle</strong> and <strong>peas</strong>, reserving a cup&nbsp;of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and keep the pot for the next step</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>baby gammon</strong>&nbsp;is done, transfer it to a board and shred it, using two forks &ndash; this technique is known as 'pulling'&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: if you don't want to pull the gammon, simply cut it up into bite-size pieces!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pot (or a&nbsp;large enough pot to fit all of the ingredients in!) to a medium heat with a very generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;the<strong> conchiglie</strong>, <strong>peas</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>shredded&nbsp;</strong><strong>ham</strong>&nbsp;with a generous splash of<strong> starchy pasta water&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1070.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>D</strong><strong>ijon mustard,&nbsp;</strong><strong>clotted cream, grated cheese</strong>&nbsp;and a squeeze of<strong>&nbsp;lemon<span style=\"color: #e86754;\">&nbsp;</span></strong>into the pot</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>chopped pea shoots </strong>and a grind of<strong> black</strong>&nbsp;<strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;and stir until the pea shoots are wilted&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cut the remaining<strong> lemon </strong>into wedges</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
